value.title: Three Christmases: Highlights of Trump's previous Mar-a-Lago holiday stays
value.excerpt: Lago will have in store this year, but his previous holidays at the Southern White House have been notable and memorable. Trump arrived on Dec. 16 and departed on Jan. 1. On his way to Palm Beach, the president-elect first stopped in Orlando for a "thank you" rally for supporters.

value.title: Pence echoes Trump on election loss in West Palm speech to conservative youths
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence on Tuesday echoed his boss' defiance in the face of re-election defeat during a speech to young conservatives.

value.title: Biden says 'our darkest days with COVID are ahead of us, not behind us'
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden spoke frankly in a rare address on the bleak reality of COVID-19 in the U.S., telling Americans "Our darkest days…are ahead of us, not behind us," during remarks on Tuesday.

value.title: News Wrap: Alex Padilla is tapped to fill Kamala Harris’ Senate seat
value.excerpt: In our news wrap Tuesday, California Secretary of State Alex Padilla is tapped to fill the U.S. Senate seat vacated by Vice President-elect Kamala Harris, the E.U.'s executive body calls for an end to travel bans aimed at confining a new COVID-19 strain in Britain,

value.title: Nancy Pelosi plans to pull Trump out of the White House 'by his hair': Report
value.excerpt: The House Speaker is said to have made the comments during discussions regarding a coronavirus relief package.

value.title: Lev Parnas files motion to dismiss, says he was selectively prosecuted to protect Trump
value.excerpt: Lev Parnas, the indicted associate of Rudy Giuliani, has filed a motion to dismiss the campaign finance charges against him, arguing he has been selectively prosecuted and blocked from providing information to lawmakers seeking to impeach President Trump.

value.title: Trump's main banker at Deutsche Bank announces her resignation
value.excerpt: The president's longstanding contact at the bank, Rosemary Vrablic, will step down on Dec. 31, though the reasons for her departure are unclear.

value.title: Even as he urges caution on COVID-19, Pence flies to Florida to speak at large event
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence has urged Americans to step up precautions, but he flew to Florida to speak to thousands at an indoor summit held by a conservative youth group.

value.title: Biden says cyberattack happened on ‘Trump’s watch when he wasn’t watching’
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden is placing blame for the serious cyber hack of numerous federal government agencies and major companies on President Trump and pledged that “we will respond” when it’s determined which county is behind the damage.

value.title: Biden: No 'obvious choice' yet for attorney general
value.excerpt: The president-elect also re-upped his commitment to not discuss his son's legal troubles with any AG candidates.

value.title: Biden hasn't discussed Hunter in his search for an AG, some stories about son were 'Russian disinformation'
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden said in a press conference Monday that his son Hunter’s business dealings had not come up in discussions about his highly anticipated pick for attorney general.

value.title: Biden says 'our darkest days' in battling Covid-19 'are ahead of us'
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden will deliver remarks ahead of Christmas in Wilmington, Delaware, on Tuesday afternoon.

value.title: Pence urges conservatives 'to stay in the fight' as 'our election' continues
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence emphasized on Tuesday that the presidential election “continues.” Speaking in West Palm Beach, Florida at a student action summit organized by Turning Point USA, a major pro-Trump and conservative youth advocacy group, the vice president urged the crowd “to stay in the fight

value.title: From Trump's impeachment trial to Hunter Biden: The biggest political scandals of 2020
value.excerpt: As 2020 comes to a close, the news has been dominated by a global pandemic, statewide lockdowns and a presidential election. Amid all that, it’s easy to forget about political events, including scandals and controversies, that otherwise would have been more in the spotlight.

value.title: Trump supporters to hold virtual 'second inauguration' on Jan. 20
value.excerpt: Thousands of supporters have pledged to attend a virtual "second inauguration" for President Trump, who lost his bid for a second term, at the same time President-elect Joe Biden is slated to be sworn in on Jan. 20.

value.title: Newsom picks Alex Padilla to fill Kamala Harris' Senate seat
value.excerpt: Gov. Gavin Newsom appointed California Secretary of State Alex Padilla to fill Vice President-elect Kamala Harris' Senate seat on Tuesday, choosing the first Latino in state history for the role.

value.title: Trump Will Face Different Twitter Rules When He Leaves Office
value.excerpt: As a public official, President Trump tweets with less risk of having his posts taken down or his account suspended. That will change on Jan. 20.

value.title: Televangelist Pat Robertson says Trump lives in an 'alternate reality' and should move on from election loss
value.excerpt: Televangelist Pat Robertson, a prominent conservative backer of Donald Trump, said Monday that the President is living in an "alternate reality" and should "move on" from his 2020 election loss.

value.title: Biden picks Connecticut schools chief as education secretary
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden has chosen the education commissioner for Connecticut and a former public school teacher to serve as education secretary

value.title: Trump issues executive order requiring 'beautiful' federal architecture
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump signed an executive order on Monday looking to ensure that federal buildings feature "beautiful" architecture, expressing a preference for classical architecture over modernist designs.

value.title: House conservatives strategize with Trump and Pence in push to challenge Biden's win
value.excerpt: Alabama GOP Rep. Mo Brooks and fellow House conservatives met privately on Monday with President Donald Trump and Vice President Mike Pence as the lawmakers prepared to mount a long-shot bid in January to overturn the Electoral College results that made Joe Biden the official winner of the election.

value.title: Biden to push for more coronavirus relief, setting up a clash with GOP
value.excerpt: Many Democrats backing the coronavirus relief bill are counting on Biden to push for another aid package shortly after taking office. But Republicans oppose another deal, setting up an early clash of wills between Biden and Senate Republicans.

value.title: Trump's conservative agenda at HHS stalled by department's office of general counsel: sources
value.excerpt: A struggle has developed within the Department of Health and Human Services (HHS) whereby President Trump's abortion and conscience-related agendas encountered roadblocks from the Office of General Counsel (OGC), multiple sources allege.

value.title: Rep. Clyburn on Trump and Operation Warp Speed: 'I'm glad he got out of the way'
value.excerpt: President Trump's greatest contribution to the success of Operation Warp Speed in developing a coronavirus vaccine was getting "out of the way," House Majority Whip James Clyburn, D-S.C., told "Your World" Monday.

value.title: Gen. Jack Keane: Biden must be 'willing to confront the Chinese Communist Party'
value.excerpt: New reports confirm China lied about the severity of the coronavirus pandemic, making the question of how the incoming Biden administration will hold Beijing accountable an urgent one, Fox News senior strategic analyst Gen. Jack Keane told "America's Newsroom" Monday.
